The South African Weather Services says KwaZulu-Natal can expect a cloudy day throughout the province. The service says although there are no storm alerts for the moment, there is a 30% chance of rain expected this afternoon with a possibility of thunderstorms. Weather forecaster Wiseman Dlamini explains the weather conditions. “Today (Saturday) over KZN we are having cloudy condition and we’ve got the possibility of thunderstorms in the afternoon. We are going for 30% chances this afternoon. On the other side, it’s going to be 50% chance over the western part of the province today. At this stage, there are no alerts for the province.” On Sunday, the western part of province can expect similar weather conditions with a chance of 60% of showers and thunder showers. 